{
  "doc_id": "43687",
  "text": "Human pituitary tumor-transforming gene (PTTG), known as securin, is a multifunctional proto-oncogene overexpressed in various tumors, including ovarian cancer [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Overexpression of PTTG in vitro induces cellular transformation and tumor development in transgenic mice [CITATION_4] . The overexpression of PTTG is correlated with tumor invasion, progression, metastasis, and angiogenesis, suggesting that PTTG may play a crucial role in tumorigenesis [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] . Until now, little was known about the effects of PTTG on the metabolic switch and proliferation process of tumor cells.",
